doc_summary_long: Nine Black Lives Matter activists have pleaded guilty to trespass charges following a protest at London City airport that disrupted the journeys of 9,000 passengers. The group has been sentenced to conditional discharges ranging from 18 months to two years. The group has faced accusations of cultural appropriation after it emerged they were all white and many had links to environmental groups.
doc_summary_short: Nine Black Lives Matter activists have pleaded guilty to trespass charges following a protest at London City airport that disrupted the journeys of 9,000 passengers.
doc_title: Black Lives Matter activists plead guilty to trespass after City airport protest
